{
  "nodes": [
    {"id":"thesis","type":"file","file":"09 - Patterns and Theses/Thesis - CENTCOM Sensor Density Hypothesis.md","x":-200,"y":-680,"width":520,"height":280,"color":"1"},
    {"id":"legend","type":"text","text":"## Sensor density, not UAP density\n\nThe geographic distribution of UAP reports in this collection tracks ==where the U.S. has sensors and mandatory reporting==, not where unusual objects preferentially appear.\n\n- CENTCOM: ~25 years of continuous, dense ISR. Largest observation-hour denominator. Dominates the corpus.\n- INDOPACOM: reporting scaled up 2023-2025; its share of the corpus grew accordingly.\n- EUCOM / SOUTHCOM / NORTHCOM / AFRICOM: near-zero reports despite global civilian UAP reporting.\n\nRead any AARO-era public statistic about UAP geography as a map of sensor geography first.","x":-1380,"y":-680,"width":660,"height":520,"color":"2"},
    {"id":"hdr-centcom","type":"text","text":"## CENTCOM\nHighest sensor + mission density. Dominant share of corpus.","x":-960,"y":-20,"width":380,"height":120,"color":"3"},
    {"id":"hdr-indopacom","type":"text","text":"## INDOPACOM\nGrowing share as reporting scaled up 2023-2025.","x":-100,"y":-20,"width":380,"height":120,"color":"3"},
    {"id":"hdr-empty","type":"text","text":"## EUCOM / SOUTHCOM / NORTHCOM / AFRICOM\nNear-zero reports.","x":760,"y":-20,"width":380,"height":120,"color":"3"},
